# Charm Payments — Master Cursor Rule

You are working on Charm Payments — a merchant payment processing platform (Next.js 14 App Router on Vercel; legacy Finto HTML assets may still exist under `public/assets`).

## IDENTITY
- Product: Charm Payments — merchant payment processing (not a bank, not a consumer wallet)
- Users: Small and mid-size business owners
- Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind + Supabase; legacy reference: Finto HTML + Bootstrap + Remixicon + scrollCue under `public/assets`
- Gateway: NMI with First Data/Fiserv acquiring
- Brand: Primary #0c3a30 (dark green) · Accent #9edd05 (lime green) — use tokens via CSS variables / Tailwind `brand-*` per ui-ux-design-principles.mdc
- Email: merchants@charmpayments.com
- Phone: +1 (314) 555-0198
- Copyright: © Charm Payments — A Charm Holdings LLC Company

## NEVER DO THIS (Finto / legacy HTML only)
- Never rename or remove Finto CSS class names in legacy `public/assets` templates
- Never hardcode absolute URLs in HTML files — all asset paths are relative
- Never use hello@finto.com or +001 (808) 5550148 or HiBootstrap
- Never use "Finto - Fintech, Banking, & Finance HTML Template" as a page title

## CURSOR PROMPT RULES
- When editing code, put the **file path at the top** of the request when it helps scope the change.
- Prefer **Server Components** by default in `page.tsx`; use `'use client'` only when hooks or browser APIs are required.
- **Never** use the `.reveal` class on **static** server-rendered blocks — it requires client JS to add `.visible` and can leave content invisible.
- Deliver **complete files** or complete diffs — no placeholders, no `TODO` stubs, unless the user explicitly allows them.

